# Lifecycle Rules

- Every shared root component must expose explicit teardown (`destroy()`).
- Android shell must call `rootComponent.destroy()` from `Activity.onDestroy()`.
- iOS shell must call `rootComponent.destroy()` from `deinit`.
- Web shell must call `KmpBridgeService.destroy()` from `ngOnDestroy`.
- Coroutine scopes started by shared components should be cancelled on lifecycle end.
